      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEAUTIFUL BANTER (1) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten 1.5 lengths, (17.58) at this track. Deserves serious consideration. MUM'S ON FIRE (2) produced a moderate effort last time when seventh at Richmond Straight over 324m behind Despicable Margo (18.47) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Has ability and can atone. POURING RAIN (3) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.42) at The Gardens behind My Octavius in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form out of her last race has been franked. Winning chance. BIG CUTIE (7) won last start in very good time. That form reads well.",
